# The Premise

> **THE KEPLER TESTIMONIES** - 500 testimonies from a vanished ship. 488 are ordinary. 12 are impossible. All are true.

## Selection Context

The community chose this premise from three AI-generated pitches:

| Pitch | Logline | Result |
|-------|---------|--------|
| THE LAST ORIGINAL | Your backed-up husband came back better. Now you can't tell if he's still him. | - |
| **THE KEPLER TESTIMONIES** | 500 testimonies from a vanished ship. 488 are ordinary. 12 are impossible. All are true. | Winner |
| TRANSLATION DISTANCE | Every conversation with the alien is an invasion of privacy. Understanding might be worth it. | - |

## What This Premise Implies

### Structural Elements
- An anthology or mosaic structure (500 testimonies)
- A mystery at the center (vanished ship)
- Contrast between mundane and extraordinary (488 vs 12)
- Epistolary/documentary format (testimonies)
- Unreliable narration paradox ("all are true")

### Questions to Explore
- What was the Kepler? (Ship name suggests space exploration)
- What does "vanished" mean? (Lost? Disappeared? Destroyed?)
- Who collected these testimonies? When? Why?
- What makes 12 of them "impossible"?
- How can contradictory testimonies all be "true"?

## Classification

- **Domain**: Story Meta
- **Stability**: Static (this is the locked premise)
- **Abstraction**: Conceptual

